{"type":"message","id":"2bd20a04","parentId":"e72f2a14","timestamp":"2026-04-30T16:32:04.009Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_QcuG5zMyUdMvGqDcL1nd2wxM|fc_00cf43d14e6c06b40169f3840291fc819781a1c1fe5eba8c66","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"poll","bracketed":false,"data":"","eof":false,"hex":[],"keys":[],"limit":400,"literal":"","offset":0,"sessionId":"ember-sage","text":"","timeout":30000},"partialJson":"{\"action\":\"poll\",\"bracketed\":false,\"data\":\"\",\"eof\":false,\"hex\":[],\"keys\":[],\"limit\":400,\"literal\":\"\",\"offset\":0,\"sessionId\":\"ember-sage\",\"text\":\"\",\"timeout\":30000}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":52552,"output":60,"cacheRead":28160,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80772,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777566717191,"responseId":"resp_00cf43d14e6c06b40169f383fee230819788647bfe5df516d9"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4fe95d1a","parentId":"2bd20a04","timestamp":"2026-04-30T16:32:31.293Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_QcuG5zMyUdMvGqDcL1nd2wxM|fc_00cf43d14e6c06b40169f3840291fc819781a1c1fe5eba8c66","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.12 (1c0672b) — I'll refactor your busywork like it owes me money.\n\nUsage: openclaw mcp [options] [command]\n\nManage OpenClaw MCP config and channel bridge\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help  Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  help        Display help for command\n  list        List configured MCP servers\n  serve       Expose OpenClaw channels over MCP stdio\n  set         Set one configured MCP server from a JSON object\n  show        Show one configured MCP server or the full MCP config\n  unset       Remove one configured MCP server\n\n---\n\n🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.12 (1c0672b) — Shell yeah—I'm here to pinch the toil and leave you the glory.\n\nUsage: openclaw mcp set [options] <name> <value>\n\nSet one configured MCP server from a JSON object\n\nArguments:\n  name        MCP server name\n  value       JSON object, for example {\"command\":\"uvx\",\"args\":[\"context7-mcp\"]}\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help  Display help for command\n\n---\n19983:        \"mcp\": {\n19985:          \"title\": \"Allow /mcp\",\n19986:          \"description\": \"Allow /mcp chat command to manage OpenClaw MCP server config under mcp.servers (default: false).\"\n40088:            \"mcporter\": {\n40094:                  \"description\": \"Routes QMD through an mcporter daemon instead of spawning qmd per request, reducing cold-start overhead for larger models. Keep disabled unless mcporter is installed and configured.\"\n40099:                  \"description\": \"Names the mcporter server target used for QMD calls (default: qmd). Change only when your mcporter setup uses a custom server name for qmd mcp keep-alive.\"\n40104:                  \"description\": \"Automatically starts the mcporter daemon when mcporter-backed QMD mode is enabled (default: true). Keep enabled unless process lifecycle is managed externally by your service supervisor.\"\n40109:              \"description\": \"Routes QMD work through mcporter (MCP runtime) instead of spawning `qmd` for each call. Use this when cold starts are expensive on large models; keep direct process mode for simpler local setups.\"\n40133:              \"description\": \"Overrides the exact mcporter tool name used for QMD searches while preserving `searchMode` as the semantic retrieval mode. Use this only when your QMD MCP server exposes a custom tool such as `hybrid_search` and keep it unset for the normal built-in tool mapping.\"\n40361:    \"mcp\": {\n40854:                    \"mcpServers\": {\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"ember-sage","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"\n🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.12 (1c0672b) — I'll refactor your busywork like it owes me money.\n\nUsage: openclaw mcp [options] [command]\n\nManage OpenClaw MCP config and channel bridge\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help  Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  help        Display help for command\n  list        List configured MCP servers\n  serve       Expose OpenClaw channels over MCP stdio\n  set         Set one configured MCP server from a JSON object\n  show        Show one configured MCP server or the full MCP config\n  unset       Remove one configured MCP server\n\n---\n\n🦞 OpenClaw 2026.4.12 (1c0672b) — Shell yeah—I'm here to pinch the toil and leave you the glory.\n\nUsage: openclaw mcp set [options] <name> <value>\n\nSet one configured MCP server from a JSON object\n\nArguments:\n  name        MCP server name\n  value       JSON object, for example {\"command\":\"uvx\",\"args\":[\"context7-mcp\"]}\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help  Display help for command\n\n---\n19983:        \"mcp\": {\n19985:          \"title\": \"Allow /mcp\",\n19986:          \"description\": \"Allow /mcp chat command to manage OpenClaw MCP server config under mcp.servers (default: false).\"\n40088:            \"mcporter\": {\n40094:                  \"description\": \"Routes QMD through an mcporter daemon instead of spawning qmd per request, reducing cold-start overhead for larger models. Keep disabled unless mcporter is installed and configured.\"\n40099:                  \"description\": \"Names the mcporter server target used for QMD calls (default: qmd). Change only when your mcporter setup uses a custom server name for qmd mcp keep-alive.\"\n40104:                  \"description\": \"Automatically starts the mcporter daemon when mcporter-backed QMD mode is enabled (default: true). Keep enabled unless process lifecycle is managed externally by your service supervisor.\"\n40109:              \"description\": \"Routes QMD work through mcporter (MCP runtime) instead of spawning `qmd` for each call. Use this when cold starts are expensive on large models; keep direct process mode for simpler local setups.\"\n40133:              \"description\": \"Overrides the exact mcporter tool name used for QMD searches while preserving `searchMode` as the semantic retrieval mode. Use this only when your QMD MCP server exposes a custom tool such as `hybrid_search` and keep it unset for the normal built-in tool mapping.\"\n40361:    \"mcp\": {\n40854:                    \"mcpServers\": {\n","name":"openclaw mcp"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1777566751018}}
